import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    median_delay = data['delay'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_delay, color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median Delay: {median_delay:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.ylabel('Distance (miles)')
    
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='ignore')
    
    airport_counts = data['origin'].value_counts() + data['destination'].value_counts()
    airport_counts = airport_counts.sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    ax = airport_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which airports have the most flights?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='ignore')
    flights_by_date = data.groupby('date').size()
    
    plt.plot(flights_by_date.index, flights_by_date.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flights by date?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
